                <head>No. 31.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Lowell</persName> to Earl <persName
                            type="to">Granville</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1882-03-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 28, 1882</date>. (Received March
                        28.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Lord</hi>: Referring to my note of yesterday, I have the
                    honor to acquaint you that I have received this morning an additional telegram
                    from Mr. Frelinghuysen, requesting me to inform your lordship that the British
                    subject Lane, on whose behalf Mr. West intervened on the 24th instant, asking
                    for a speedy trial, is now being tried. It appears that all the delays and
                    continuances in this case have been made on the motion of Lane’s counsel.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>J. R. LOWELL.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
